Script,Benjamin2D
window.currentPBSScenario = 'Benjamin2D';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Benjamin_2D';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for Benjamin2D');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'Benjamin2D',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: 21GF-PolishTwoSuiters
convention-card-ew: 21GF-GIB
auction-filter: Auction.....\n2[CD] +
*/
# Game Forcing Benjamin 2D
dealer south

gC = clubs(south)>4    and top3(south,clubs)==3    or top5(south,clubs)==4
gD = diamonds(south)>4 and top3(south,diamonds)==3 or top5(south,diamonds)==4
gH = hearts(south)>4   and top3(south,hearts)==3   or top5(south,hearts)==4
gS = spades(south)>4   and top3(south,spades)==3   or top5(south,spades)==4

suits1 = gC or gD or gH or gS
suits2 = (gC and gD) or (gC and gH) or (gC and gS) or (gD and gH) or (gD and gS) or (gH and gS)

oneSuit = suits1 and shape(south,any 8xxx +any 7xxx +any 6xxx)
twoSuit = suits2 and shape(south,any 76xx +any 75xx +any 66xx +any 65xx +any 55xx)
bal = not (twoSuit or oneSuit)

C1 = hcp(south)>17 and hcp(south)<25 and twoSuit
C2 = hcp(south)>19 and hcp(south)<25 and oneSuit and not twoSuit
CB = hcp(south)>22 and hcp(south)<25 and bal
DU = hcp(south)>23 and not bal
DB = hcp(south)>24 and bal

twoC = C1 or C2 or CB
twoD = DU or DB


### Imported Leveling Code ###
c1 = hascard(west,2C)
c2 = hascard(east,2D)
c3 = hascard(west,3C)
c4 = hascard(east,3D)

keep06 = c1 and c2          // this is used later w/c3 & c4 expressions
keep44 = c3 or c4           // this is used later w/c1 & c2 expressions

keep015 = keep06 and c3
keep03 = keep06 and keep44
keep045 = keep06 and not c3
####06 = c1 and c2
keep11 = c1 and keep44
keep14 = c1 and not keep44
keep19 = c1 and not c2
keep25 = c1
keep30 = keep06 or c3
keep33 = c1 or (c2 and keep44)
####44 = c3 or c4
keep47 = keep44 or keep06

keep53 = not keep47
keep56 = not keep44
keep67 = not keep33
keep70 = not keep30
keep75 = not keep25
keep81 = not keep19
keep86 = not keep14
keep89 = not keep11
keep94 = not keep06
keep955 = not keep045
keep97 = not keep03
keep985 = not keep015
keep   = 1
keep0  = 0
### End of Imported Leveling Code ###

lev-C1 = C1 and keep
lev-C2 = C2 and keep
lev-CB = CB and keep

lev-DU = DU and keep
lev-DB = DB and keep
levelTheDeal = lev-C1 or lev-C2 or lev-CB or lev-DU or lev-DB

# Now do it
twoC or twoD
and levelTheDeal

action printoneline,
action printoneline,
average "C 1-suit" 100 * C1,
average "C 2-suit" 100 * C2,
average "C bal   " 100 * CB,
average "Open 2C " 100 * twoC,

average "D unbal " 100 * DU,
average "D bal   " 100 * DB,
average "open 2D " 100 * twoD,
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Benjamin 2 Bid (Lev),\n\
--- Benjamin 2 Bid - 2!C strong & 2!D Game Forcing\n\
• 2!C shows 18-19 w/very strong 2-suiter，20-22 unbalanced w/very good suit，or 23-24 bal，Responses are...\n\
  • 2!D 7-HCP，continue by bidding 4-card suits up the line\n\
  • 2!H 5+HCP and 5+!H\n\
  • 2!S 5+HCP and 5+!S\n\
  • 2NT 8+HCP and balanced hand \n\
• 2!D shows 23+ unbalanced or 24+ balanced -- GAME FORCE，responses are...\n\
  • 2NT 5-HCP，no 5-card major\n\
  • 2!H/!S 5+!H/!S\n\
  • 3!C/!D 6+!C/!D\n\
This is leveled so that 2!C and 2!D occur at about the same frequency.\n\
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benjamin_Twos\n\
%Benjamin2D%,width=50% backgroundColor=lightpink
